Rattata is a small, quadruped rodent Pokémon. Its most notable feature is its large teeth. Like most rodents, its teeth grow continuously throughout its life and must be worn down by gnawing. The top half of its body is light purple, while the lower half is cream-colored. It has a pair of thin, cream-colored whiskers and a long tail that curls at the tip. Rattata has purple fur on its back, and cream fur on its stomach. Females have shorter whiskers and lighter fur color.

Tyranitar is a large, bipedal, dinosaurian pokémon with a green, armeth'r-like encave cov'ring its corse. T hast two pairs of did point teeth: one in the upp'r chap and one in the base'r. Sev'ral spikes of varying size protrude from the backeth of its headeth, neck, and shouldst'rs. Both sides of its chest, the cent'r of its backeth, and its hams has't two triangular holes. Th're is a grizzled, diamond-shap'd patch of scales cov'ring its belly, and a bawbling'r one on its backeth. T hast three claws on its feet and hands. A ringeth of spikes surrounds the tipeth of its tail

Mega tyranitar hast m're gaps in its armeth'r than its n'rmal f'rm, with four new triangular holes 'long the sides of its neck and one on its throat. The four on its chest art anon larg'r with the top two enwheeling r'd ovals

Lugia is a large pokémon yond resembles a dragon, a plesiosaur, and a bird. T is primarily whey-face silv'r-white, but t hast blue und'rsides with slightly varying tones. T hast a ridg'd that from which we speak similar to a beak, although t hast did point teeth on its base'r chap. Its headeth hast a pointeth to the backeth, and lugia’s eyes has't did point blue 'r black spikes on those folk. Lugia hast a longeth, slend'r neck and a smooth, streamlin'd corse. Dark blue 'r black plate-like protrusions runneth down the length of its backeth, and th're art two bawbling'r, m're did point ones on the endeth of its tail. T can foldeth backeth these plates to increaseth its speedeth

Ho-oh is an avian pokémon resembling a phoenix and a peacock. Its feath'rs art predominantly gold and red, with yellow tail-feath'rs, a white und'rside, and green feath'rs at the tipeth of its wings. Ho-oh hast a green stripe on its neck, a yellow beak, black rings 'round its r'd eyes, and a feath'red, yellow crest on its headeth. Ho-oh's wings art prismatic, causing t to trail a rainbow behind t. T hast darkly col'r'd feet and forks with four toes and longeth talons

Bagon is a bipedal, blue, reptilian pokémon vaguely resembling pachycephalosaurus. T possesses a large, round snout, triangular eyes, yellow, circular ears similar to reptiles, and a yellow base'r chap with two teeth protruding upwards. Three thick, grizzled ridges cov'r the top of its headeth, and continueth downwards to cov'r its neck as well. Th're is a triangular patch of yellow on its und'rside. T hast stubby, digitless arms and sh'rt forks with two toes on each foot

Shelgon is a quadrup'd pokémon yond resembles a pupal stage. Th're art bone structures cov'ring its corse, which f'rm a shell with two openings and three ridges on top. One opening is in front, revealing two yellow eyes, while the oth'r opening is in the backeth. This bony cov'ring repels foe attacks, but t maketh shelgon heavy

Salamence is a quadruped, draconic pokémon with a longeth, tapeth'ring tail. T is primarily blue with a grizzled base'r chap and thickly did scale und'rside. Th're art r'd markings on its throat, the und'rside of its tail, and stripes on the inn'r surface of its forks. Additionally, th're art hath raised r'd ridges above its eyes. Three champain fins protrude from eith'r side of its headeth, possibly acting in the same mann'r yond a canard wouldst on an aircraft

As mega salamence, its wings meld togeth'r into a single huge, crescent-shap'd wing. Acc'rding to the anime, the hard, yet v'ry flexible prop'rties of its wings alloweth those folk to beest hath used as blades in mid-air battles. Its visage, neck, corse and tail art narrow'r, and its tail is noticeably sh'rt'r in length. The ridges above its eyes art anon far less prominent, and t nay longeth'r possesses the thick, grizzled scaling ov'r its base'r chap. Instead, the smooth r'd flesh und'rneath hast been hath left exposed, increasing its streamlineth compliment extern

Asbeldum is a robotic pokémon yond hast a longeth corse with a setteth of claws sticking out of its rear endeth. T hast one large, r'd eye in the cent'r of its nearly sph'rical headeth, which is setteth into a ball-and-socket joint at its front endeth. A sh'rt crest projects from its corse and extends ov'r its headeth. Coequal though beldum is a mechanical creature, t still hast emotions, the needeth to consume, and a way of reproducing

Metang is a robotic pokémon with teal, metallic skin. T hast a disc-shap'd corse with a pair of champain, grizzled spikes on eith'r side toward the rear. A jet cannot scratcheth metang due to its stout corse. Th're is a grizzled spike in the middle of its visage, similar to a nose. A pair of r'd eyes reside in two holes in its metallic skin. While t appears to want forks, t hast a pair of thick arms with three claws on the ends

Metagross is a robotic pokémon with a turquoise, disc-shap'd corse and four forks. The main corse appears to s'rve as both headeth and corse, and this pokémon's ov'rall construction gives t the compliment extern of a mechaniz'd arachnid. T uses its heavy corse to pin down its prey bef're consuming those folk with its large that from which we speak. A large, metallic crosseth is situat'd in the cent'r of its visage

Mega metagross, t constantly floats, and its forks becometh arms. The crosseth on its visage turns whey-face gold, and t gains two bawbling holes and a spike immediately below the crosseth, giving the impression of a goatee. Its multiple brains processeth inf'rmation simultaneously, enabling t to calmly assesseth the tide of a hurlyburly and defeat its opponent with accuracy

Regirock is a large golem madeth of brown rocks. Regirock hast an 'range patt'rn on its visage yond resembles a capital lett'r "h". T hast longeth arms with jutting shouldst'rs and club-like hands, its forks art sh'rt in comparison to its corse. Th're is a line of rocky spines running down its backeth. At which hour t gets did damage in hurlyburly 'twill searcheth f'r new rocks to repaireth itself

Regice is compos'd of antarctic ice yond resembles a crystal. Its visage hast an unusual patt'rn consisting of seven yellow dots in a "+" f'rmation. T hast four spikes on its backeth. Its forks art conical and t balances its entire corse on those two points. Th're art three fing'rs on each of its cylindrical arms

The top-half of registeel's corse is sph'rical and grizzled with a black stripe running down its "face". Its visage consists of seven r'd dots in a hexagonal f'rmation. T hast black arms with three fing'rs each and cylindrical forks. While registeel hast been did classify as a steel-type pokémon, its corse is actually madeth of a mat'rial yond is hard'r than any known metal

It has triangular ears and a blue face with a white oval in the middle

Kyogre is a massive whale-like pokémon with two big pect'ral fins, each with four white square-shap'd nails. T hast a deep blue corse and a white chin area with two bawbling spikes protruding und'r t. Above each eye art two white, oval-shap'd spots. T hast r'd stripes 'round its chin, eyes, d'rsal fins, and t'rso. These stripes gloweth at which hour kyogre is brimming with pow'r. The tail is tatt'r'd with four trailing parts, the inn'r ones being bawbling'r than the out'r. Its eyes art bawbling, yellow, and shadow'd with black

Primal kyogre is similar to kyogre, but t grows to m're than twice its usual size. Its skin col'r changes to a dark'r shadeth of blue. The four trailing parts of its tail art consid'rably longeth'r and champain at the ends, and each has't half-translucent webbing down the middle. Its f'rehead anon hast the ? symbol, which is did connect to the two large oval-shap'd spots and tail, and lighteth blue ? symbols art seen on each pect'ral fin, connecting to the out'r nails with a r'd marking connecting to the inn'r nails
